`AmazonKeyManagementServiceConfig.UserAgent` is a read-only property. This is not very convenient in some scenarios.

One of the main advantages of AWS Key Management Service (KMS) is a detailed audit of every request made to the service. When multiple of my services make requests to the same KMS endpoints, as a customer I want to be able to distinguish services in the audit logs. Unfortunately, I won't be able to do that.

Since `AmazonKeyManagementServiceConfig.UserAgent` is read-only, I'm not able to set a custom string there, and UserAgent for all requests from all my services that use .NET SDK will be the same.

## Expected Behavior
`AmazonKeyManagementServiceConfig.UserAgent`  should be read-write property.

## Current Behavior
`AmazonKeyManagementServiceConfig.UserAgent` is a read-only property

## Possible Solution
Change the code in `AmazonKeyManagementServiceConfig` to
```
        public override string UserAgent
        {
            get
            {
                return _userAgent;
            }
            set
            {
                _userAgent = value;
            }
        }
```

Please, let me know if a proposed solution looks good and I can prepare a PR.

